# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: HuntingTheBeast1
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah placed one hand on the Mayor's shoulder."
    new "Sarah placed one hand on the Mayor's shoulder."

    old "I promise you I will do everything I can to help your village."
    new "I promise you I will do everything I can to help your village."

    old "She saw a smile come across the man's face."
    new "She saw a smile come across the man's face."

    old "Really? You'll actually help us?"
    new "Really? You'll actually help us?"

    old "I had almost feared to even ask..."
    new "I had almost feared to even ask..."

    old "Most soldiers are not know for their kindness to common folk."
    new "Most soldiers are not know for their kindness to common folk."

    old "Perhaps. But when I grew up my father showed me the importance of helping those who are in need."
    new "Perhaps. But when I grew up my father showed me the importance of helping those who are in need."

    old "Your father sounds like a kind man."
    new "Your father sounds like a kind man."

    old "He was."
    new "He was."

    old "The Mayor stood up."
    new "The Mayor stood up."

    old "I think the best place for you to start is to speak with Garret."
    new "I think the best place for you to start is to speak with Garret."

    old "Garret?"
    new "Garret?"

    old "He is the town's Huntsman. He has spend more time tracking the beast than any other."
    new "He is the town's Huntsman. He has spend more time tracking the beast than any other."

    old "He also knows the land better than anyone. He can help you get started."
    new "He also knows the land better than anyone. He can help you get started."

    old "Thank you, I'll go speak with him and see about resolving this matter."
    new "Thank you, I'll go speak with him and see about resolving this matter."

    old "The Mayor grabbed her hands just before she left."
    new "The Mayor grabbed her hands just before she left."

    old "Thank you...truly."
    new "Thank you...truly."

    old "Leaving the tavern, Sarah walk through the streest of Hillstown, following the directions to the Huntman's hut."
    new "Leaving the tavern, Sarah walk through the streest of Hillstown, following the directions to the Huntman's hut."

    old "Throughout the town, Sarah saw there were still some celebrations, but they seemed to have dimmed a bit."
    new "Throughout the town, Sarah saw there were still some celebrations, but they seemed to have dimmed a bit."

    old "The news of the attack on the young girl seemed to have spoiled anyone's appetite for a party."
    new "The news of the attack on the young girl seemed to have spoiled anyone's appetite for a party."

    old "Winding down the road, Sarah came upon a small hut near the edge of the town."
    new "Winding down the road, Sarah came upon a small hut near the edge of the town."

    old "A large man sat just outside, carving into a block of wood with a knife."
    new "A large man sat just outside, carving into a block of wood with a knife."

    old "The man was build like a wall, tall and broad shoulders. Arms like logs."
    new "The man was build like a wall, tall and broad shoulders. Arms like logs."

    old "Sarah had expected the man to look like a Huntsman, but she had not expected him to look almost like an exaggerated ideal of it."
    new "Sarah had expected the man to look like a Huntsman, but she had not expected him to look almost like an exaggerated ideal of it."

    old "Before she could announce herself, he spoke."
    new "Before she could announce herself, he spoke."

    old "His voice boomed loud and deep, fitting for a man like himself."
    new "His voice boomed loud and deep, fitting for a man like himself."

    old "I was told people in small towns have better manners than big city types."
    new "I was told people in small towns have better manners than big city types."

    old "Well whoever told you that must have been an idiot."
    new "Well whoever told you that must have been an idiot."

    old "The Huntsman continued carving the wooden figurine."
    new "The Huntsman continued carving the wooden figurine."

    old "You are Garret, the town Huntsman?"
    new "You are Garret, the town Huntsman?"

    old "And you are the Rose Knight, I take it."
    new "And you are the Rose Knight, I take it."

    old "Sarah was surprised to hear him call her that."
    new "Sarah was surprised to hear him call her that."

    old "I...who told you that?"
    new "I...who told you that?"

    old "Your soldiers like to blabber after a few drinks in them."
    new "Your soldiers like to blabber after a few drinks in them."

    old "They talk all sorts of nonesense about you, killing demons and what not."
    new "They talk all sorts of nonesense about you, killing demons and what not."

    old "And there aren't a lot of blonde women walking around in suits of armor. So the odds were decent it was you."
    new "And there aren't a lot of blonde women walking around in suits of armor. So the odds were decent it was you."

    old "You have a proper name, or just a title?"
    new "You have a proper name, or just a title?"

    old "Sarah smiled. The man was coarse in his language, but she appreciated his directness."
    new "Sarah smiled. The man was coarse in his language, but she appreciated his directness."

    old "Sarah Rose."
    new "Sarah Rose."

    old "Well, good to meet you, Sarah Rose, though I regret the circumstances."
    new "Well, good to meet you, Sarah Rose, though I regret the circumstances."

    old "So you know about the girl?"
    new "So you know about the girl?"

    old "The Miller girl? Yes."
    new "The Miller girl? Yes."

    old "Gossip goes through this town like a plague. Terrible what happened to her."
    new "Gossip goes through this town like a plague. Terrible what happened to her."

    old "You think she'll live?"
    new "You think she'll live?"

    old "Garret shrugged."
    new "Garret shrugged."

    old "She's tougher than she looks. I've said my prayers and burned my offerings to the Gods."
    new "She's tougher than she looks. I've said my prayers and burned my offerings to the Gods."

    old "Whatever happens after is out of my hands."
    new "Whatever happens after is out of my hands."

    old "Sarah watched as he continued to carve the wood with the tip of his knife."
    new "Sarah watched as he continued to carve the wood with the tip of his knife."

    old "Shouldn't you be out gathering men? Go hunt for this thing now that the tracks are still fresh?"
    new "Shouldn't you be out gathering men? Go hunt for this thing now that the tracks are still fresh?"

    old "Garret sighed."
    new "Garret sighed."

    old "I did that. I did that for Gods know how many times."
    new "I did that. I did that for Gods know how many times."

    old "Always the same shit."
    new "Always the same shit."

    old "The Beast is gone before we even hear about the attack, and when we get there, the tracks lead back into the forest."
    new "The Beast is gone before we even hear about the attack, and when we get there, the tracks lead back into the forest."

    old "Then they vanish."
    new "Then they vanish."

    old "So, you've just given up? Taken to carving toys?"
    new "So, you've just given up? Taken to carving toys?"

    old "Not a toy. A totem."
    new "Not a toy. A totem."

    old "Totem?"
    new "Totem?"

    old "The forests here are old. Home to spirits of all kinds."
    new "The forests here are old. Home to spirits of all kinds."

    old "We carve totems as offerings, to keep them at peace when we enter the forest."
    new "We carve totems as offerings, to keep them at peace when we enter the forest."

    old "Why would a spirit care for a totem?"
    new "Why would a spirit care for a totem?"

    old "They're woodland spirits. They can sense the trees and the wood more clearly than any other substance."
    new "They're woodland spirits. They can sense the trees and the wood more clearly than any other substance."

    old "So we carve them into shapes from their old lives. Small things they might remember."
    new "So we carve them into shapes from their old lives. Small things they might remember."

    old "By remembering that they were once people, the spirits calm down a bit."
    new "By remembering that they were once people, the spirits calm down a bit."

    old "You don't strike me as the superstitious type."
    new "You don't strike me as the superstitious type."

    old "It ain't superstitious if it's fact."
    new "It ain't superstitious if it's fact."

    old "That's true enough, I suppose. That still doesn't resolve our issue."
    new "That's true enough, I suppose. That still doesn't resolve our issue."

    old "Garret put down the knife and the totem."
    new "Garret put down the knife and the totem."

    old "What business is this of yours anyway?"
    new "What business is this of yours anyway?"

    old "From what I take it, you have an army and quite the reputation. Shouldn't someone like you be out saving the world?"
    new "From what I take it, you have an army and quite the reputation. Shouldn't someone like you be out saving the world?"

    old "What do you care what happens to a small town like this?"
    new "What do you care what happens to a small town like this?"

    old "I care. Blame my personality. Blame how I was raised. Fuck, if I knew how to turn it off, I would."
    new "I care. Blame my personality. Blame how I was raised. Fuck, if I knew how to turn it off, I would."

    old "But I can't. So instead, I end up wasting my time talking to angry, old hunters, trying to convince them to accept some help."
    new "But I can't. So instead, I end up wasting my time talking to angry, old hunters, trying to convince them to accept some help."

    old "Garret looked up at her. For the first time there was somewhat of a smile on his face."
    new "Garret looked up at her. For the first time there was somewhat of a smile on his face."

    old "I ain't that old, young sprout."
    new "I ain't that old, young sprout."

    old "Sarah followed Garret into his home."
    new "Sarah followed Garret into his home."

    old "It was well kept, but plain. The type of home one might expect of a Huntsman in a town out nowhere."
    new "It was well kept, but plain. The type of home one might expect of a Huntsman in a town out nowhere."

    old "I've been hunting this thing for months now, and still ain't even caught sight of the thing."
    new "I've been hunting this thing for months now, and still ain't even caught sight of the thing."

    old "Sarah watched as Garret unfurled a map."
    new "Sarah watched as Garret unfurled a map."

    old "It showed the town, the surrounding areas, the forest, and a few red markers."
    new "It showed the town, the surrounding areas, the forest, and a few red markers."

    old "Garret placed his finger near one of the red markers."
    new "Garret placed his finger near one of the red markers."

    old "These are the known places where we've had attacks. About a doze or so now."
    new "These are the known places where we've had attacks. About a doze or so now."

    old "A dozen attacks?"
    new "A dozen attacks?"

    old "Not all as serious as the others."
    new "Not all as serious as the others."

    old "He tapped at three markings in quick succession."
    new "He tapped at three markings in quick succession."

    old "Those are the three deaths...the killings."
    new "Those are the three deaths...the killings."

    old "The other attacks, thank the Gods, were only injuries."
    new "The other attacks, thank the Gods, were only injuries."

    old "Studying the map, she tried to uncover a pattern."
    new "Studying the map, she tried to uncover a pattern."

    old "They all take place outside the village."
    new "They all take place outside the village."

    old "Garret nodded."
    new "Garret nodded."

    old "As far as we know, the Beast avoids the town. But even just a small distance outside, we've had attacks."
    new "As far as we know, the Beast avoids the town. But even just a small distance outside, we've had attacks."

    old "They're mostly on this side."
    new "They're mostly on this side."

    old "Sarah tapped the northern portion of the map."
    new "Sarah tapped the northern portion of the map."

    old "It's closer to the forest edge."
    new "It's closer to the forest edge."

    old "We're all but certain that it hides out there, though we've not been able to track it to a lair."
    new "We're all but certain that it hides out there, though we've not been able to track it to a lair."

    old "You think it has a lair?"
    new "You think it has a lair?"

    old "Fucked if I know, to tell you the truth. Everything I know about animals has gone out the window since this thing showed up."
    new "Fucked if I know, to tell you the truth. Everything I know about animals has gone out the window since this thing showed up."

    old "Why do you think it attacks?"
    new "Why do you think it attacks?"

    old "Garret frowned."
    new "Garret frowned."

    old "Well, it doesn't do it for food, clearly."
    new "Well, it doesn't do it for food, clearly."

    old "But it also seems to avoid humans to a degree. It doesn't go into the town. So why? Why attack outside the forest at all."
    new "But it also seems to avoid humans to a degree. It doesn't go into the town. So why? Why attack outside the forest at all."

    old "Garret looked at the map intently."
    new "Garret looked at the map intently."

    old "I don't know, Sarah. I wish I had more answers for you."
    new "I don't know, Sarah. I wish I had more answers for you."

    old "Sarah studied the map a moment longer."
    new "Sarah studied the map a moment longer."

    old "They said you know these forests better than most, is that true?"
    new "They said you know these forests better than most, is that true?"

    old "Grew up here as a kid. My father was a Huntsman before me, taught me and my sister everything we knew."
    new "Grew up here as a kid. My father was a Huntsman before me, taught me and my sister everything we knew."

    old "Your sister?"
    new "Your sister?"

    old "Garret's face grew dark."
    new "Garret's face grew dark."

    old "She's not around anymore. Died during a particularly bad storm a few years back."
    new "She's not around anymore. Died during a particularly bad storm a few years back."

    old "Life out here, I suppose."
    new "Life out here, I suppose."

    old "Sarah could hear in his voice that there was still a pain beneath his cold exterior."
    new "Sarah could hear in his voice that there was still a pain beneath his cold exterior."

    old "And about the timings of the attacks..."
    new "And about the timings of the attacks..."

    old "All night."
    new "All night."

    old "Whatever it is, it never comes out during the day."
    new "Whatever it is, it never comes out during the day."

    old "For a while, each was quiet."
    new "For a while, each was quiet."

    old "So, you got any great ideas?"
    new "So, you got any great ideas?"

    old "Sarah considered for a while."
    new "Sarah considered for a while."

    old "The Mayor wanted me to march my whole army through the forest. Sweep through every corner."
    new "The Mayor wanted me to march my whole army through the forest. Sweep through every corner."

    old "Garret laughed."
    new "Garret laughed."

    old "Of course he would say something like that."
    new "Of course he would say something like that."

    old "But if you want to keep your army, I suggest you don't."
    new "But if you want to keep your army, I suggest you don't."

    old "Those forests are old, but they also run deep."
    new "Those forests are old, but they also run deep."

    old "They extend from here, all the way up north to the mountains, and around there, they turn into swamplands."
    new "They extend from here, all the way up north to the mountains, and around there, they turn into swamplands."

    old "The truth is, even if you could send your men that deep, they would still be bogged down by the swamps."
    new "The truth is, even if you could send your men that deep, they would still be bogged down by the swamps."

    old "And this Beast may very well live deeper still."
    new "And this Beast may very well live deeper still."

    old "So numbers aren't going to solve this..."
    new "So numbers aren't going to solve this..."

    old "She stared at the map intently."
    new "She stared at the map intently."

    old "What if I lured it out?"
    new "What if I lured it out?"

    old "Lured it?"
    new "Lured it?"

    old "Yeah. Go in there with a small group. See if it attacks us?"
    new "Yeah. Go in there with a small group. See if it attacks us?"

    old "Maybe, but the creature doesn't attack for weeks on end. You might very well be out there for a long time."
    new "Maybe, but the creature doesn't attack for weeks on end. You might very well be out there for a long time."

    old "Sarah sighed. She certainly didn't have weeks."
    new "Sarah sighed. She certainly didn't have weeks."

    old "Perhaps you need more information."
    new "Perhaps you need more information."

    old "This map...it's fine, but you need to see the real lay of the land."
    new "This map...it's fine, but you need to see the real lay of the land."

    old "I can take you into the forest. Show you the tracks of the creature."
    new "I can take you into the forest. Show you the tracks of the creature."

    old "It wasn't without danger, but then again, she didn't see many other options."
    new "It wasn't without danger, but then again, she didn't see many other options."

    old "Besides, she herself was plenty strong and Garret looked as if he'd be able to fend for himself."
    new "Besides, she herself was plenty strong and Garret looked as if he'd be able to fend for himself."

    old "Fine. Let's set out for the forest."
    new "Fine. Let's set out for the forest."

    old "Tomorrow night."
    new "Tomorrow night."

    old "That fast?"
    new "That fast?"

    old "I can't keep my army waiting around for too long."
    new "I can't keep my army waiting around for too long."

    old "I see...it's fast, but it should be doable."
    new "I see...it's fast, but it should be doable."

    old "I'll start preparing right away. Come back here tomorrow night and we'll head out."
    new "I'll start preparing right away. Come back here tomorrow night and we'll head out."

    old "Sarah nodded and thanked Garret for his help so far."
    new "Sarah nodded and thanked Garret for his help so far."

    old "Leaving his house, she walked the now empty streets of Hillstown."
    new "Leaving his house, she walked the now empty streets of Hillstown."

    old "A fear had descended over the city, one that had snuffed out any semblance of celebration."
    new "A fear had descended over the city, one that had snuffed out any semblance of celebration."

    old "Sarah wondered what she had truly gotten herself into."
    new "Sarah wondered what she had truly gotten herself into."

    old "The day after went by quickly."
    new "The day after went by quickly."

    old "When the news went out that they would not march for another few days, most of the soldiers seemed to take it well enough."
    new "When the news went out that they would not march for another few days, most of the soldiers seemed to take it well enough."

    old "After all the hard marching, most were eager to but their bags down for longer than a day."
    new "After all the hard marching, most were eager to but their bags down for longer than a day."

    old "Sarah herself spend little time on managing her company, instead, she had fretted over what would come that night."
    new "Sarah herself spend little time on managing her company, instead, she had fretted over what would come that night."

    old "When the sun started to go down, she set out to the edge of town and found Garret already waiting by the road."
    new "When the sun started to go down, she set out to the edge of town and found Garret already waiting by the road."

    old "I've got one pack for myself and another for you."
    new "I've got one pack for myself and another for you."

    old "I hope you can carry your weight."
    new "I hope you can carry your weight."

    old "Sarah reached down and slung the backpack over her shoulders."
    new "Sarah reached down and slung the backpack over her shoulders."

    old "I've marched plenty in my life, with more weight on my back than a mule."
    new "I've marched plenty in my life, with more weight on my back than a mule."

    old "Just hope you can keep up with me, old man."
    new "Just hope you can keep up with me, old man."

    old "She heard Garret laugh as she walked up the road ahead of him."
    new "She heard Garret laugh as she walked up the road ahead of him."

    old "Walking on the road, it wasn't long before the town and it's noises faded away."
    new "Walking on the road, it wasn't long before the town and it's noises faded away."

    old "Before long, it was only herself and Garret. The quiteness that could be found in places like these."
    new "Before long, it was only herself and Garret. The quiteness that could be found in places like these."

    old "I just realized it's been a while since things have been this quiet..."
    new "I just realized it's been a while since things have been this quiet..."

    old "Usually I march with my men. Make camp with the others. There is always some noise, anywhere you go."
    new "Usually I march with my men. Make camp with the others. There is always some noise, anywhere you go."

    old "It's almost strange to just hear nothing but nature."
    new "It's almost strange to just hear nothing but nature."

    old "It's not all bad, living out here."
    new "It's not all bad, living out here."

    old "The two continued to walk until the road took them to the outskirts of the forest."
    new "The two continued to walk until the road took them to the outskirts of the forest."

    old "The treeline quickly grew thick."
    new "The treeline quickly grew thick."

    old "Sarah realized she couldn't look more than a few paces into the forest."
    new "Sarah realized she couldn't look more than a few paces into the forest."

    old "Wow, it's really dense."
    new "Wow, it's really dense."

    old "Only gets worse the deeper you get."
    new "Only gets worse the deeper you get."

    old "No more than a few minutes and you'll struggle to even keep a steady pace."
    new "No more than a few minutes and you'll struggle to even keep a steady pace."

    old "People go in there, unprepared, they can end up lost. More than a few people found their deaths that way."
    new "People go in there, unprepared, they can end up lost. More than a few people found their deaths that way."

    old "Good thing I have you."
    new "Good thing I have you."

    old "Garret only nodded."
    new "Garret only nodded."

    old "Seeing how easy it was to get lost, Sarah fell back and allowed Garret to take the lead."
    new "Seeing how easy it was to get lost, Sarah fell back and allowed Garret to take the lead."

    old "She was surprised at the struggle it took to keep up with him."
    new "She was surprised at the struggle it took to keep up with him."

    old "Where he skillfully dodged and stepped past each branch or bush, she seemed constantly bogged down."
    new "Where he skillfully dodged and stepped past each branch or bush, she seemed constantly bogged down."

    old "I don't think my armor is much suited for a forest like this."
    new "I don't think my armor is much suited for a forest like this."

    old "She saw Garret turn and look at her as he kept walking."
    new "She saw Garret turn and look at her as he kept walking."

    old "Let me know if you fall too far behind. I don't want you getting lost in here and having to go find you."
    new "Let me know if you fall too far behind. I don't want you getting lost in here and having to go find you."

    old "Sarah wandered if it was genuine concern for her safety, or if he just didn't want to be inconvenienced."
    new "Sarah wandered if it was genuine concern for her safety, or if he just didn't want to be inconvenienced."

    old "Despite it all, the continued to make progress, going deeper and deeper into the forest."
    new "Despite it all, the continued to make progress, going deeper and deeper into the forest."

    old "When she had first heard the Mayor tell her that they could not find the Beast, she had been somewhat surprised."
    new "When she had first heard the Mayor tell her that they could not find the Beast, she had been somewhat surprised."

    old "But now that she was experiencing the forest herself, she came to understand."
    new "But now that she was experiencing the forest herself, she came to understand."

    old "No more than a few paces left or right, and she could essentially see nothing."
    new "No more than a few paces left or right, and she could essentially see nothing."

    old "A creature hiding could ask for no more perfect place."
    new "A creature hiding could ask for no more perfect place."

    old "Suddenly, the forest broke and gave way to a small clearing."
    new "Suddenly, the forest broke and gave way to a small clearing."

    old "It seemed as if the space had been cleared out by hand. Small remnants of a campfire remained."
    new "It seemed as if the space had been cleared out by hand. Small remnants of a campfire remained."

    old "Marching through the forest can be dangerous for many reasons. Getting lost is one of them."
    new "Marching through the forest can be dangerous for many reasons. Getting lost is one of them."

    old "But there are other dangers. Certain parts of the forest are so thick they barely allow you to even make camp."
    new "But there are other dangers. Certain parts of the forest are so thick they barely allow you to even make camp."

    old "That's why we cut out small plots like these."
    new "That's why we cut out small plots like these."

    old "Travel from hub to hub, and you can manage to make good progress and still get a decent night of sleep."
    new "Travel from hub to hub, and you can manage to make good progress and still get a decent night of sleep."

    old "You made all this?"
    new "You made all this?"

    old "Most of the villagers never go far beyond the edges of the forest."
    new "Most of the villagers never go far beyond the edges of the forest."

    old "And there aren't many hunters left in the village."
    new "And there aren't many hunters left in the village."

    old "Most make their living farming these days. More stable. Easier."
    new "Most make their living farming these days. More stable. Easier."

    old "Sarah threw down her backpack and sat down near the campfire."
    new "Sarah threw down her backpack and sat down near the campfire."

    old "Gathering two pieces of flint and some tinder, she quickly managed to bring the fire to life."
    new "Gathering two pieces of flint and some tinder, she quickly managed to bring the fire to life."

    old "She saw Garret look at her, somewhat surprised."
    new "She saw Garret look at her, somewhat surprised."

    old "Nothing, I was just surprised."
    new "Nothing, I was just surprised."

    old "That I know how to make a campfire? You live on the road for long enough, you learn it sooner or later."
    new "That I know how to make a campfire? You live on the road for long enough, you learn it sooner or later."

    old "Or did you take me for a princess?"
    new "Or did you take me for a princess?"

    old "Garret laughed as he put down his own backpack and joined her at the fire."
    new "Garret laughed as he put down his own backpack and joined her at the fire."

    old "It's hard what to make of you. Not really quite a soldier and not really quite a princess."
    new "It's hard what to make of you. Not really quite a soldier and not really quite a princess."

    old "Sarah smiled. She wondered if he knew how true that was."
    new "Sarah smiled. She wondered if he knew how true that was."

    old "Can't say the same for you."
    new "Can't say the same for you."

    old "You're a Huntsman, I would have known that even if nobody had told me."
    new "You're a Huntsman, I would have known that even if nobody had told me."

    old "Garret smiled in the way he often seemed to do. Mirthless."
    new "Garret smiled in the way he often seemed to do. Mirthless."

    old "My father was the same."
    new "My father was the same."

    old "I like to think I was so different from him growing up, but I guess I ended up pretty much like him."
    new "I like to think I was so different from him growing up, but I guess I ended up pretty much like him."

    old "Sarah saw his eyes lost in a memory."
    new "Sarah saw his eyes lost in a memory."

    old "And your sister?"
    new "And your sister?"

    old "The word 'sister' caused a deep pain to run through his face."
    new "The word 'sister' caused a deep pain to run through his face."

    old "She and I were twin souls, if such a thing can exist."
    new "She and I were twin souls, if such a thing can exist."

    old "It was as if I could read her mind and she mine. A glance. A small gesture. Enough to speak volumes."
    new "It was as if I could read her mind and she mine. A glance. A small gesture. Enough to speak volumes."

    old "Sarah smiled. She could relate, she and Thomas had been much the same."
    new "Sarah smiled. She could relate, she and Thomas had been much the same."

